      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHY SHOULD SHE (7) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when third (16.72) at Murray Bridge Straight. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from four starts. Likely to be in the finish again. DEL MAR TAMMY (2) was impressive last time, posting an effortless 3.5 lengths win in taking a Maiden in 22.17 and a new Best time this course and distance. Expecting another bold showing. ALL THE SPOILS (1) has an honest record despite remaining a maiden and overdue for a win, having placed 12 of 24 career runs. The form from her last run stacks up well. A big run wouldn't surprise. VISIBILITY (8) cannot be left out after placing here at this trip last start.",
